<TEXT>
baiestecatherine quebec ap prince andrew has become the 
prince of whales 
britains duke of york and his duchess sarah ferguson adopted 
an endangered beluga and named it white mischief the couple took 
the action monday while on a whalewatching tour from this port on 
the st lawrence river about 125 miles northeast of quebec city 
the newest and largest addition to the royal family wasnt seen 
however and in fact hasnt been seen since 1987 
the royal couple on a 13day canadian tour join 44 other people 
who have paid 5000 each to adopt belugas white whales about 12 
feet long prince andrews whale however was a gift from the 
