family tree monday showing his links to an english couple who 
married in leiden in 1603 the president was in the netherlands for 
a 24hour stop the last in his 10day journey 
bush appreciated very much that his lineage had been fleshed 
out said pieter de baar a research assistant for schelhaas 
a small community of english protestant dissenters lived in 
leiden for more than a decade before setting sail for america in the 
early 17th century 
bush is a direct 12th generation descendant of francis cooke and 
his canterburyborn wife hester mahieu according to schelhaas 
records 
little is known about the cookes except their marriage date june 
4 1603 and that they had three children including their daughter 
jane cooke a bush ancestor born here in 1615 
according to the leiden records bushs roots can also be traced 
to another pilgrim family the sisters abigail and sarah jenney 
both born in leiden and daughters of a brewers apprentice john 
jenney and his wife sarah carey 
bushs father was related to abigail jenney as well as to the 
cookes and his mother is a descendant of sarah 
