the chronicler of stalinist terror was sent abroad after western 
publishers published his magnum opus the gulag archipelago a 
critique of soviet rule since its birth in the 1917 bolshevik 
revolution 
in his nobel lecture solzhenitsyn condemned the persecution of 
millions of soviets including writers he urged his fellow authors 
to describe reality as they saw it not as dictated by communist 
authorities 
the whole of our national literature lies buried not only 
without clothes but also without underwear naked tagged on the 
toe but not for a minute was russian literature interrupted 
although it was left aside 
solzhenitsyn urged writers to take what he called a simple step 
for a simple brave man do not take part in lies do not support 
lying actions 
defeat the lie he wrote 
do not make excuses do not give up the joys of life but 
enter the struggle one word can pull the world together 
novy mir has a circulation of 15 million and publication of the 
speech gave russian readers their first sanctioned taste of the 
banned writer since the same journal published his novella one 
day in the life of ivan denisovich 27 years ago 
