to convince voters to support a tax increase cut nearly a half 
billion dollars from the state budget 
the 491 million in budget cuts included a 210 million reduction 
in state aid to cities and towns for such things as schools and 
police a 97 million cut in human services and 62 million from 
education 
the explanation dukakis gives for the state fiscal situation is 
that revenue taken in by tax collectors plummeted over the past two 
