of the 650 members of parliament had gone home 
lord hailsham britains former chief legal officer called the 
vote unrepresentative and foolish 
you cant test a mans vocation to become a priest by a 
majority in parliament it has to be done by the church 
authorities he said 
the ban on ordination for remarried divorced men or those whose 
spouses have been divorced has long been regarded as an anomaly in 
the church of england because ordained clergy can be divorced 
without losing their posts 
