<TEXT>
the berlin philharmonic orchestra will wait until 
october to begin searching in earnest for a successor to maestro 
herbert von karajan and one critic suggested the process could take 
years 
karajan conductor of the philharmonic for 34 years died sunday 
at 81 
klaus geitel a respected music critic living in west berlin 
said other conductors could be tied up for years with longterm 
contracts elsewhere 
sure they could ask riccardo muti or someone else to take over 
for karajan he said but the big question is could they 
accept 
muti conducts the philadelphia orchestra and milans la scala 
bernd gellermann the berlin philharmonics business director 
said the orchestra is now on summer break and wont even try in 
earnest to find a replacement for karajan until october 
the berlin philharmonic is one of the worlds most famous 
orchestras its marriage to the celebrated karajan reflected its 
place in germanys heritage of musical excellence and composing 
geniuses like ludwig van beethoven and johann sebastian bach 
music fans suffered an initial shock in april when karajan 
announced he was ending his often stormy relationship with the 
orchestra they were buffeted a second time when karajan died 
he was buried monday night in a small ceremony in his hometown 
near salzburg austria 
musicians critics and fans already were wondering who would 
replace karajan after he resigned as the orchestras conductor for 
life 
orchestra musicians and administrators are highly secretive about 
possible heirs but they made it clear this week that only the best 
conductors in the world are in the running 
i could name nine or 10 people but i wont said rudolph 
watzel a double bass player in the berlin orchestra for 21 years 
the orchestras members make recommendations for karajans 
successor so watzel is in a position to know who the top candidates 
are 
gellermann said karajan will in any case be a hard act to follow 
the successor will be taking over an enormous legacy he said 
he said karajans replacement will come from a group of 
conductors who have already worked with the orchestra 
west german music writers say the frontrunners are guest 
conductors who have been on karajans podium during his absences due 
to illness or who have conducted the orchestra since he announced 
his resignation the orchestra may have to continue to rely on guest 
conductors during the search for a permanent conductor 
the berliner morgenpost newspaper said tuesday that the likely 
contenders to replace karajan include seiji ozawa of the boston 
symphony orchestra james levine of the metropolitan opera in new 
york and muti 
all have lifted the baton in karajans place in recent months 
guest conductors are a venerable tradition at the 107yearold 
philharmonic such musical giants as johannes brahms antonin 
dvorak richard strauss and peter tchaikovsky performed historic 
concerts with the orchestra in its early years 
karajans contemporaries have taken his place over the past few 
years when he missed performances because of chronic back problems 
medical treatment and generally declining health 
karajan had not conducted the berlin orchestra since dec 31 
1988 
