two families and a 23yearold man 
seven people in all escaped over border barriers tuesday from 
communist east germany western border police reported 
two east german couples crossed the border with their sons aged 
5 and 8 in the luechowdannenberg area 75 miles southeast of 
hamburg said west german border police in hanover 
a police statement said one woman was slightly injured climbing a 
steel mesh fence but the other five members of the group were 
unhurt and the escape apparently went unnoticed by east german 
border guards 
west german police in kassel said a 23yearold east german truck 
driver escaped into hesse state early tuesday in the 
hersfeldrotenberg area 95 miles northeast of frankfurt 
they said the young man was able to avoid east german border 
guards even though he set off an acoustic alarm shortly before 
climbing a steel mesh fence 10 feet high to reach west germany 
at least 10 east germans have fled to the west in the past week 
the ministry of intergerman relations in bonn said earlier in 
july that 332 east germans had crossed into west berlin or west 
germany during the first six months of 1989 last year 590 escapes 
were reported 
