president bush declared parts of texas and 
louisiana major disaster areas tuesday as a result of the havoc 
wreaked there last month by tropical storm allison 
the white house announced the disaster declarations shortly after 
bushs return from a 10day trip to europe 
nine texas counties were made eligible for federal aid hardin 
harris jasper jefferson liberty newton orange san jacinto and 
tyler 
in louisiana the parishes of allen beauregard calcasieu east 
baton rouge grant iberville natchitoches pointe coupee rapides 
and winn were made eligible for help 
the federal emergency management agency will handle the 
assistance which can include temporary housing grants lowcost 
loans to cover uninsured property losses and other programs to help 
the areas recover from the storm and its flooding 
fema named graham l nance as federal coordinating officer for 
the recovery in texas and robert d broussard for louisiana both 
work out of the regional fema office in denton texas 
bush later declared connecticut eligible for disaster aid to help 
it recover from the severe storms winds and tornadoes that struck 
the western part of the state beginning july 10 
the declaration will provide relief for individuals and local 
governments in the counties of new haven and litchfield 
albert a gammal jr of femas boston regional officer was 
appointed to coordinate the federal recovery operations 
