of emergency ross maggio called the gangster by inmates for 
his unwavering adherence to rules was brought in as warden to scour 
away the blood and filth 
by most accounts he succeeded food was improved wretched 
dining halls were cleaned prisoners were kept busy with work in the 
fields and organized recreation more guards were hired and given 
better pay 
the prison seemed dormant for almost a decade until four murders 
four suicides 64 stabbings and 11 escapes in 14 months forced 
polozola to declare a new state of emergency june 21 another 
suicide occurred earlier this month 
the fury at angola is hidden behind the concertina wire the 
grounds are trim and neat guard towers rise above white fences 
rows of corn and herds of cattle the prison camps look washed and 
the steel bars are painted 
