<TEXT>
a year after the first major roman catholic 
schism in a century the vatican admits it has been unable to 
curtail the ultratraditionalist movement of marcel lefebvre the 
rebel archbishop 
both sides say lefebvre has gained thousands of followers since 
he was excommunicated for consecrating four bishops in defiance of 
papal orders 
cardinal paul augustin mayer head of a papal commission charged 
in july 1988 with keeping traditionalists in the church says many 
bishops resist a vatican effort to make the old latin mass more 
available 
among traditionalist catholics there is an attitude of 
desperation and because of that an evergreater number of them 
consider returning to monsignor lefebvre as the only possible 
response the west german cardinal said in an interview with the 
italian catholic monthly 30 giorni 30 days 
some catholics believe the church should be cautious with 
compromise church sources said the presidents of the bishops 
conferences of england france west germany and switzerland told 
pope john paul ii in may he was going too far in wooing 
traditionalists 
lefebvre 83 rejects the reforms of the 196265 second vatican 
council including acceptance of religious freedom celebration of 
the mass in local languages and interfaith cooperation 
john paul said after the schism june 30 1988 that followers of 
the french archbishop faced excommunication unless they renounced 
him but even the threat of expulsion the churchs gravest 
punishment has not hindered the movement 
spokesmen for lefebvre said only 16 priests had left his st pius 
x fraternity based in switzerland since the split with the vatican 
and 34 had been ordained bringing the number of priests to 222 
they said the number of faithful had increased by 10 percent to 
15 percent the papal commission serving traditionalists ecclesia 
dei said attendance at lefebvre churches in many areas had grown by 
30 percent 
an overall view of the statistics would indicate this 
particular challenge is not being effectively met on the part of the 
official church structure said a vatican official familiar with 
the work of ecclesia dei speaking on condition of anonymity 
he said the lefebvre movement was growing in leaps and bounds 
in the united states and expanding in france australia and south 
america 
ecclesia dei officials say the attraction of the renegade 
movement is mostly its use of the 16th century latin tridentine 
mass which was suppressed after vatican ii in the new mass the 
local language is used and the priest faces the congregation instead 
of the altar 
cardinal mayer said in the interview with 30 giorni that many 
bishops have ignored the popes request a year ago to make full 
and generous application of a 1984 decree allowing the tridentine 
rite to be used in special circumstances 
lay people know this and their response in england france 
america has been to turn to the st pius x fraternity of monsignor 
lefebvre he said 
the lefebvre movement claims millions of sympathizers and vatican 
estimates put its membership at 100000 to 12 million the roman 
catholic church has about 850 million members 
an official at the us national catholic conference of bishops 
familiar with the traditionalist issue said privately the vast 
overwhelming majority of american catholics support the new mass 
he also said the lefebvre movement goes far beyond preference for 
the latin mass to embrace social economic and political stances 
lefebvre is an ardent anticommunist some officials of his 
movement say they doubt the holocaust in which the nazis killed 6 
million jews during world war ii in may a frenchman accused of 
crimes against humanity as head of a pronazi militia was captured 
in a french priory run by lefebvre followers 
in october the vatican recognized the fraternity of st peter a 
traditionalist order led by a former lefebvre official the 
fraternity with 18 priests and 30 seminarians encourages 
lefebvres followers to return to the church 
ecclesia dei has granted special permission to more than 150 
priests to use the old mass and has received scores more requests 
from priests who chose to ask the vatican instead of their local 
bishop 
vatican efforts to blunt the impact of his renegade movement have 
irritated lefebvre making it unlikely the church will be able to 
heal its first major schism since the old catholics left the church 
in 1870 over the issue of papal infallibility 
they are waging an indecent war against us lefebvre was 
quoted as saying in 30 giornis latest issue how is it possible 
to have a dialogue with these men 
