<DOCNO> AP890718-0237 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
the commodity futures trading commission is 
curtailing its control over exotic investment products known as 
hybrids such as bonds linked to the price of oil or bank rates 
tied to the consumer price index 
hybrids are so named because they are financial instruments 
combining some aspects of commodity futures and options with the 
characteristics of debt securities such as bonds or bank deposits 
examples of these hybrid instruments include a bank deposit with 
its interest rate indexed to the exchange rate of the dollar and the 
japanese yen or a corporate note with its yield tied to the price 
of gold or oil 
new rules the cftc approved monday detailed the types of hybrids 
that will be exempt from its scrutiny including debt securities 
already regulated by the securities and exchange commission time 
deposits offered by a bank insured by the federal deposit insurance 
corp or instruments where the value of the option part has a 
premium of no more than 40 percent of the instruments issue price 
the hybrid issue has been controversial since 1987 when the the 
cftc which regulates futures and commodity options markets first 
proposed that such new investment instruments be regulated by the 
commission and traded only on organized exchanges 
but hybrid investment product issuers complained that such 
regulation would kill the development of a potential 
multibilliondollar market 
in january the commission voted 50 to remove some kinds of 
hybrid instruments from its control and formalized that vote monday 
thereby facilitating continued innovation and competition in these 
and related markets said cftc chairwoman wendy l gramm 
some have argued that the commission should not make any 
statements in these areas arguing that the regulatory uncertainty 
that exists was created by the commissions unwarranted assertion of 
jurisdiction this simply is not true said ms gramm in a 
statement 
regulatory uncertainty results because these innovative 
instruments by their very nature tend to cut across established 
regulatory and jurisdictional boundaries she said 
the cftc also voted to issue to a policy statement on the kinds 
of swap transactions it will not regulate because of jurisdictional 
limits 
interestrate and currency swaps are widely used to manage risks 
in world financial markets in a typical interestrate swap one 
party such as a bank strapped with by fixedrate customer loans 
exchanges its fixedrate debt for an equivalent amount of 
floatingrate debt to alter its interestrate exposure 
the international swap dealers association breathed a sigh of 
relief after an 18month debate with regulators over the issue 
isda chairman mark c brickell said us dealers were now free to 
develop swap options and commodity swaps of all types including 
swaps of physical commodities and financial indices this enables 
us dealers and endusers to play on a level field with their 
worldwide competitors 
the cftc criteria bar marketing a swap to the public and require 
that the swap be undertaken within the parties lines of business 
the commission said it will continue to review swaps that do not 
meet its criteria on a casebycase basis 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

