incumbent would be subject to review and certainly parallel 
treatment is fair said gonzalez 
as chairman of the house banking committee gonzalez has blamed 
wall as a major contributor to the escalation of the sampl crisis by 
underestimating its magnitude in 1987 and 1988 
wall however has support from garn the ranking republican on 
the senate banking committee wall was director of the senate 
committees staff from 1981 through 1986 when garn was its chairman 
and his wife is now the senators personal secretary 
house negotiators rejected the senates proposal to put 
statechartered thrifts which have been blamed for a large part of 
the crisis under the regulation of the new office that wall might 
assume 
instead they insisted monday that seidman be put in control of 
statechartered sampls while the new treasury office assumes 
responsibility for regulating federally chartered thrifts 
the house conferees also agreed monday to adopt tougher senate 
language restricting business activities of statechartered thrifts 
and giving the fdic authority to suspend deposit insurance if an sampl 
has no tangible capital 
but they could not agree on how to reconcile the way junk bonds 
are treated the house wants to make sampls dispose of all junk bonds 
within two years the senate last week proposed cutting how much of 
an sampls deposits can be invested in the highyield securities from 
the 11 percent now allowed to 6 percent 
the biggest issue still dividing the two sides is over financing 
the immediate 50 billion needed to pay off depositors in failed 
institutions 
bush and the senate would do it through 30year private bonds to 
avoid swelling the federal deficit while the house would have the 
treasury borrow the money directly but exempt it from grammrudman 
deficitreduction targets 
