jumped 31 percent while another major investment firm painewebber 
group inc posted a 151 million profit after only breaking even 
for the same quarter a year ago 
both firms cited improved market conditions 
a third investment firm morgan stanley group inc said its 
secondquarter fell 171 percent from record results a year earlier 
but still was its second best quarterly performance ever 
merrill lynch the brokerage underwriting and investment 
services giant based in new york said it earned 702 million or 
62 cents per share in the three months ended june 30 compared with 
535 million or 47 cents a share a year earlier 
total revenue rose 26 percent to a record 31 billion from 25 
billion a year earlier excluding interest and dividends revenue 
rose 12 percent 
william a schreyer chairman and chief executive and daniel p 
tully president said the firms consumer market business had solid 
revenue increases in virtually all of its operations while its 
capital markets business retained the top ranking among the worlds 
debt and equity underwriters 
commission revenue rose 18 percent to 462 million reflecting 
higher equity trading volume and increased sales of money market 
instruments revenue from trading and other activities in its own 
portfolio rose 3 percent to 462 million while interest and 
dividend revenue rose to 51 percent to 139 billion 
