a federal court jury ordered the bessemer amp 
lake erie railroad on tuesday to pay 2435 million in damages in an 
antitrust case brought by steelmakers truck lines and a dock 
company 
but the railroad which plans to appeal the verdict said in a 
statement that several important motions remained before the court 
that could significantly reduce or eliminate the award 
bample also said it expected the damage verdict to be offset by 
payments from settlements by other defendant railroads 
litigation is expected to continue in the case for years 
the bample intends to pursue all of its appellate rights in 
seeking to correct what it believes to be totally inappropriate 
findings spokesman robert n gentile said 
ten suits were filed against the bample and other railroads in 1983 
and 1984 contending they conspired to block the development of 
selfunloading ore boats forcing steel companies to rely on the 
railroads to receive ore shipments 
