norfolk southern corp settled out of court during the trial the 
bample was the only defendant to proceed to a verdict in the case 
among the plaintiffs were sharon steel corp national steel 
corp wheelingpittsburgh steel corp ltv corp tauro trucking 
co ambrosia trucking and erie dock co 
the judgment returned tuesday was in a consolidation of the suits 
the case was heard by two juries the first one found the bample 
guilty on june 19 of violating antitrust laws the second jury 
charged with determining damages returned its decision tuesday 
after four days of deliberations 
