<TEXT>
general dynamics corp reported tuesday its 
secondquarter earnings improved despite an an aftertax charge of 
50 million or 120 per share associated with the ssn 688class 
attack submarine at the companys electric boat division 
the defense contractor reported earnings of 584 million or 
139 per share on sales of 25 billion during the second quarter 
for the second quarter of 1988 the company earned 467 million or 
111 per share on sales of 24 billion 
the results for the second quarter of 1988 reflected an aftertax 
charge of 33 million or 79 cents per share associated with the 
same attack submarine program 
for the first half of 1989 general dynamics earned 1338 
million or 320 per share on sales of 49 billion compared a 
profit of 1324 million or 315 per share on sales of 49 
billion for the same period in 1988 
the companys backlog was reported to have reached a record high 
including a funded backlog of 179 billion and total backlog of 
288 billion representing approximately three years in sales at 
the same time in 1988 the backlogs were listed at 167 billion 
funded and 238 billion total 
we have been advising since 1987 that the outlook for the ssn 
688class attack submarine program at electric boat has been 
uncertain said stanley c pace chairman and chief executive 
officer 
pace said general dynamics has stopped recognizing electric boat 
earnings and that additional charges will be recognized in the 
future continuing shortages of qualified new englandarea workers 
and productivity that has been lower than anticipated resulted in 
the rescheduling of work and the extension of electric boat delivery 
rates pace said 
cited by pace for improved performance during the second quarter 
were the land systems and general aviation segments of the company 
the company achieved higher profitability rate on its m1 tank 
program through advanced manufacturing techniques and cost 
containments pace said and the cessna aircraft unit achieved a 
substantial increase in its citation business jets sales 
